name: Bulbasaur
flavorText: While it is young, it uses the nutrients that are stored in the seed on its back in order to grow.
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Ivysaur
flavorText: Exposure to sunlight adds to its strength. Sunlight also makes the bud on its back grow larger.
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Venusaur ex
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, you may heal 60 damage from 1 of your Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused and Poisoned.

name: Charmander
flavorText: From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.
Attack1Text: Discard a Stadium in play.

name: Charmeleon
flavorText: If it becomes agitated during battle, it spouts intense flames, incinerating its surroundings.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Charizard ex
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon has any damage counters on it, this attack does 100 more damage.
Attack2Text: Discard 3 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Squirtle
flavorText: When it feels threatened, it draws its limbs inside its shell and sprays water from its mouth.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks.

name: Wartortle
flavorText: It cleverly controls its furry ears and tail to maintain its balance while swimming.
Attack1Text: Put up to 3 Basic Water Energy cards from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Blastoise ex
Ability1Text: This Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Discard up to 2 Basic Water Energy cards from your hand. This attack does 140 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Caterpie
flavorText: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Grass Pokemon, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Metapod
flavorText: Even though it is encased in a sturdy shell, the body inside is tender. It can't withstand a harsh attack.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks.

name: Butterfree
flavorText: It collects honey every day. It rubs honey onto the hairs on its legs to carry it back to its nest.
Attack1Text: Switch out your opponent's Active Pokemon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. Shuffle that Pokemon and all attached cards into their deck, and then shuffle this Pokemon and all attached cards into your deck. If your opponent has no Benched Pokemon, this attack does nothing.

name: Weedle
flavorText: Its poison stinger is very powerful. Its bright-colored body is intended to warn off its enemies.

name: Kakuna
flavorText: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of attacks used by your opponent's Pokemon done to this Pokemon. (Damage is not an effect.)

name: Beedrill
flavorText: May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.
Attack1Text: If you have no cards in your hand, this attack does 120 more damage, and your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned.

name: Pidgey
flavorText: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Pidgeotto
flavorText: Very protective of its sprawling territorial area, this Pokemon will fiercely peck at any intruder.

name: Pidgeot
flavorText: It spreads its gorgeous wings widely to intimidate enemies. It races through the skies at Mach-2 speed.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokemon.

name: Rattata
flavorText: This Pokemon is common but hazardous. Its sharp incisors can easily cut right through hard wood.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Raticate
flavorText: Its whiskers are essential for maintaining its balance. No matter how friendly you are, it will get angry and bite you if you touch its whiskers.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Spearow
flavorText: Due to its short wings, it can't fly long distances. It wanders about restlessly and pecks at bug Pokemon.
Ability1Text: If you go second, this Pokemon can evolve during your first turn.

name: Fearow
flavorText: Carrying food through Fearow's territory is dangerous. It will snatch the food away from you in a flash!
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Ekans
flavorText: The eggs of bird Pokemon are its favorite food. It swallows eggs whole, so sometimes an egg gets stuck, and Ekans faints.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Arbok ex
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.
Attack2Text: Your opponent discards 2 cards from their hand.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Lightning Energy card and attach it to this Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Raichu
flavorText: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.
Ability1Text: When 1 of your Pokemon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokemon, you may move a Lightning Energy from that Pokemon to this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 50 damage to itself.

name: Sandshrew
flavorText: It burrows into the ground to create its nest. If hard stones impede its tunneling, it uses its sharp claws to shatter them and then carries on digging.
Ability1Text: Trainer cards in your opponent's discard pile can't be put into their deck by an effect of your opponent's Item or Supporter cards.

name: Sandslash
flavorText: It climbs trees by hooking on with its sharp claws. Sandslash shares the berries it gathers, dropping them down to Sandshrew waiting below the tree.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Nidoran ♀
flavorText: It uses its hard incisor teeth to crush and eat berries. The tip of a female Nidoran's horn is a bit more rounded than the tip of a male's horn.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Nidorina
flavorText: If the group is threatened, these Pokemon will band together to assault enemies with a chorus of ultrasonic waves.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 Pokemon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Nidoqueen
flavorText: It pacifies offspring by placing them in the gaps between the spines on its back. The spines will never secrete poison while young are present.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from Basic Pokemon.

name: Nidoran ♂
flavorText: Small but brave, this Pokemon will hold its ground and even risk its life in battle to protect the female it's friendly with.

name: Nidorino
flavorText: It's nervous and quick to act aggressively. The potency of its poison increases along with the level of adrenaline present in its body.

name: Nidoking
flavorText: Nidoking prides itself on its strength. It's forceful and spirited in battle, making use of its thick tail and diamond-crushing horn.
Ability1Text: If you have Nidoqueen in play, ignore all Energy in the costs of attacks used by this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Clefairy
flavorText: Its adorable behavior and cry make it highly popular. However, this cute Pokemon is rarely found.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 Clefairy and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Clefable
flavorText: Their ears are sensitive enough to hear a pin drop from over a mile away, so they're usually found in quiet places.
Attack1Text: Switch in 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon to the Active Spot.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Pokemon is Knocked Out by damage from this attack, take 1 more Prize card.

name: Vulpix
flavorText: As each tail grows, its fur becomes more lustrous. When held, it feels slightly warm.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Ninetales ex
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.
Attack2Text: If you have the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent, this attack does 140 more damage.

name: Jigglypuff
flavorText: When its huge eyes waver, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Supporter card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Wigglytuff ex
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon has any Special Energy attached, it gets +100 HP.
Attack1Text: If you played a Supporter card from your hand during this turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Zubat
flavorText: Zubat live in caves, down where the sun's light won't reach. In the morning, they gather together to keep each other warm as they sleep.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, you may have your opponent reveal their hand.

name: Golbat
flavorText: Its feet are tiny, but this Pokemon walks skillfully. It sneaks up on sleeping prey before sinking in its fangs and slurping up blood.
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Oddish
flavorText: During the day, it stays in the cold underground to avoid the sun. It grows by bathing in moonlight.

name: Gloom
flavorText: What appears to be drool is actually sweet honey. It is very sticky and clings stubbornly if touched.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may look at the top 3 cards of your deck and attach any number of Basic Energy cards you find there to your Pokemon in any way you like. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

name: Vileplume
flavorText: The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may look at the top 8 cards of your deck and attach any number of Basic Energy cards you find there to your Pokemon in any way you like. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

name: Paras
flavorText: The mushrooms, known as tochukaso, are controlling the bug. Even if the bug bugs the mushrooms, they tell it to bug off.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Parasect
flavorText: The bug is mostly dead, with the mushroom on its back having become the main body. If the mushroom comes off, the bug stops moving.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. Search your deck for a number of Grass Pokemon up to the number of heads and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Venonat
flavorText: Poison oozes from all over its body. It catches small bug Pokemon at night that are attracted by light.

name: Venomoth
flavorText: The wings are covered with dustlike scales. Every time it flaps its wings, it looses highly toxic dust.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused. During your opponent's next turn, they can't play any Item cards from their hand.

name: Diglett
flavorText: It lives about one yard underground, where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears aboveground.

name: Dugtrio
flavorText: Its three heads bob separately up and down to loosen the soil nearby, making it easier for it to burrow.

name: Meowth
flavorText: All it does is sleep during the daytime. At night, it patrols its territory with its eyes aglow.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, switch in 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon to the Active Spot.

name: Persian
flavorText: Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Giovanni's Charisma card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Psyduck
flavorText: It is constantly wracked by a headache. When the headache turns intense, it begins using mysterious powers.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, whenever they flip a coin, treat it as tails.

name: Golduck
flavorText: When it swims at full speed using its long, webbed limbs, its forehead somehow begins to glow.
Attack1Text: Put up to 4 Pokemon from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Mankey
flavorText: It lives in groups in the treetops. If it loses sight of its group, it becomes infuriated by its loneliness.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokemon also does 20 damage to itself. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Primeape
flavorText: It becomes wildly furious if it even senses someone looking at it. It chases anyone that meets its glare.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon isn't Confused, this attack does nothing.

name: Growlithe
flavorText: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.
Attack1Text: Discard a Water Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Arcanine
flavorText: An ancient picture scroll shows that people were captivated by its movement as it ran through prairies.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 Basic Fire Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Fire Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Poliwag
flavorText: In rivers with fast-flowing water, this Pokemon will cling to a rock by using its thick lips, which act like a suction cup.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Poliwhirl
flavorText: This Pokemon's sweat is a slimy mucus. When captured, Poliwhirl can slither from its enemies' grasp and escape.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Poliwrath
flavorText: Poliwrath is skilled at both swimming and martial arts. It uses its well-trained arms to dish out powerful punches.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 150 more damage.

name: Abra
flavorText: Abra can teleport in its sleep. Apparently the more deeply Abra sleeps, the farther its teleportations go.

name: Kadabra
flavorText: This Pokemon's telekinesis is immensely powerful. To prepare for evolution, Kadabra stores up psychic energy in the star on its forehead.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Alakazam ex
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack can be used even if this Pokemon is on the Bench.

name: Machop
flavorText: Always brimming with power, it passes time by lifting boulders. Doing so makes it even stronger.
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

name: Machoke
flavorText: Its formidable body never gets tired. It helps people by doing work such as the moving of heavy goods.
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

name: Machamp
flavorText: With four arms that react more quickly than it can think, it can execute many punches at once.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, flip a coin. If heads, this Pokemon is not Knocked Out, and its remaining HP becomes 10.
Attack1Text: Discard the top 2 cards of your opponent's deck.

name: Bellsprout
flavorText: Its bud looks like a human face. Because of the bud, it is rumored to be a type of legendary mandrake plant.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Weepinbell
flavorText: It spits out Poison Powder to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of Acid.

name: Victreebel
flavorText: Once ingested into this Pokemon's body, even the hardest object will melt into nothing.
Attack2Text: At the end of your opponent's next turn, put 12 damage counters on the Defending Pokemon.

name: Tentacool
flavorText: This Pokemon is mostly made of water. A Tentacool out in the ocean is very hard to spot, because its body blends in with the sea.

name: Tentacruel
flavorText: Its 80 tentacles can stretch and shrink freely. Tentacruel ensnares prey in a net of spread-out tentacles, delivering venomous stings to its catch.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 90 damage for each heads. If the first flip is tails, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Geodude
flavorText: It uses both hands to climb precipitous cliffs. People who see it in action have been known to take up bouldering.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Graveler
flavorText: It travels by rolling down cliffs. If it falls into a river, it will explode with its last gasp.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

name: Golem ex
Attack1Text: During your next turn, attacks used by this Pokemon do 120 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Ponyta
flavorText: If you've been accepted by Ponyta, its burning mane is mysteriously no longer hot to the touch.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Rapidash
flavorText: The fastest runner becomes the leader, and it decides the herd's pace and direction of travel.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.
Attack2Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Slowpoke
flavorText: It is incredibly slow and dopey. It takes five seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon, and it recovers from all Special Conditions.

name: Slowbro
flavorText: When a Slowpoke went hunting in the sea, its tail was bitten by a Shellder. That made it evolve into Slowbro.
Attack1Text: Both Active Pokemon are now Asleep.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon evolved during this turn, this attack does nothing.

name: Magnemite
flavorText: The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which allows it to float.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 60 damage to itself.

name: Magneton
flavorText: Three Magnemite are linked by a strong magnetic force. Earaches will occur if you get too close.
Attack1Text: Put up to 2 Item cards from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Farfetch'd
flavorText: They use a plant stalk as a weapon, but not all of them use it in the same way. Several distinct styles of stalk fighting have been observed.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.

name: Doduo
flavorText: The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with a telepathic power.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Dodrio
flavorText: An odd species that is rarely found. The three heads respectively represent joy, sadness, and anger.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may put 1 damage counter on this Pokemon. If you do, draw a card.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.

name: Seel
flavorText: Thanks to its thick fat, cold seas don't bother it at all, but it gets tired pretty easily in warm waters.

name: Dewgong
flavorText: It sunbathes on the beach after meals. The rise in its body temperature helps its digestion.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Grimer
flavorText: Born from sludge, these Pokemon now gather in polluted places and increase the bacteria in their bodies.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon's Retreat Cost is Colorless more.

name: Muk
flavorText: It's thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, attacks used by the Defending Pokemon cost Colorless more, and its Retreat Cost is Colorless more.

name: Shellder
flavorText: It is encased in a shell that is harder than diamond. Inside, however, it is surprisingly tender.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Cloyster
flavorText: Cloyster that live in seas with harsh tidal currents grow large, sharp spikes on their shells.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 80 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Gastly
flavorText: It wraps its opponent in its gas-like body, slowly weakening its prey by poisoning it through the skin.

name: Haunter
flavorText: It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless shuddering.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may put a Supporter card from your opponent's discard pile into their hand.

name: Gengar
flavorText: To steal the life of its target, it slips into the prey's shadow and silently waits for an opportunity.
Attack1Text: Your opponent reveals their hand. This attack does 50 damage for each Trainer card you find there.
Attack2Text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Benched Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Onix
flavorText: It rapidly bores through the ground at 50 mph by squirming and twisting its massive, rugged body.
Attack1Text: Discard the top 5 cards of your deck. This attack does 80 damage for each Pokemon with a Retreat Cost of exactly 4 that you discarded in this way.

name: Drowzee
flavorText: It remembers every dream it eats. It rarely eats the dreams of adults because children's are much tastier.

name: Hypno
flavorText: When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of psi moves, such as Hypnosis and Confusion.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may make your opponent's Active Pokemon Asleep.

name: Krabby
flavorText: If it senses danger approaching, it cloaks itself with bubbles from its mouth so it will look bigger.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for up to 2 Basic Water Energy cards and attach them to this Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Kingler
flavorText: Its oversized claw is very powerful, but when it's not in battle, the claw just gets in the way.
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

name: Voltorb
flavorText: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Electrode
flavorText: The more energy it charges up, the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.
Attack1Text: Before doing damage, you may discard any number of Pokemon Tools from your Pokemon. This attack does 40 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Exeggcute
flavorText: These Pokemon get nervous when they're not in a group of six. The minute even one member of the group goes missing, Exeggcute become cowardly.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

name: Exeggutor
flavorText: When they work together, Exeggutor's three heads can put out powerful psychic energy. Cloudy days make this Pokemon sluggish.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Cubone
flavorText: This Pokemon wears the skull of its deceased mother. Sometimes Cubone's dreams make it cry, but each tear Cubone sheds makes it stronger.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is on your Bench, attacks used by your Marowak do 30 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Marowak
flavorText: When this Pokemon evolved, the skull of its mother fused to it. Marowak's temperament also turned vicious at the same time.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Hitmonlee
flavorText: The legs freely contract and stretch. The stretchy legs allow it to hit a distant foe with a rising kick.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Hitmonchan
flavorText: Its punches slice the air. However, it seems to need a short break after fighting for three minutes.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokemon (even if this Pokemon is Knocked Out), put 3 damage counters on the Attacking Pokemon.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's Excited Punch attack does 60 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Lickitung
flavorText: Bug Pokemon are Lickitung's main food source. This Pokemon paralyzes its prey with a lick from its long tongue, then swallows the prey whole.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't attack.

name: Koffing
flavorText: Its body is full of poisonous gas. It floats into garbage dumps, seeking out the fumes of raw, rotting trash.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Weezing
flavorText: Very rarely, a sudden mutation can result in two small Koffing twins becoming conjoined as a Weezing.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is in the Active Spot and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokemon, flip a coin. If heads, the Attacking Pokemon is Knocked Out.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Rhyhorn
flavorText: It can remember only one thing at a time. Once it starts rushing, it forgets why it started.
Attack1Text: Switch out your opponent's Active Pokemon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokemon.)

name: Rhydon
flavorText: Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.
Attack2Text: If you played Giovanni's Charisma from your hand during this turn, this attack does 140 more damage.

name: Chansey
flavorText: This kindly Pokemon lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokemon or people.
Ability1Text: If you took this Pokemon as a face-down Prize card during your turn and your Bench isn't full, before you put it into your hand, you may put it onto your Bench. If you put this Pokemon onto your Bench in this way, flip a coin. If heads, take 1 more Prize card.

name: Tangela
flavorText: Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this Pokemon's true appearance remains a mystery.
Attack1Text: If you played Erika's Invitation from your hand during this turn, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Kangaskhan ex
Attack1Text: Draw 3 cards.
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 100 damage for each heads.

name: Horsea
flavorText: They swim with dance-like motions and cause whirlpools to form. Horsea compete to see which of them can generate the biggest whirlpool.

name: Seadra
flavorText: Seadra's mouth is slender, but its suction power is strong. In an instant, Seadra can suck in food that's larger than the opening of its mouth.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if the Defending Pokemon tries to use an attack, your opponent flips 2 coins. If either of them is tails, that attack doesn't happen.

name: Goldeen
flavorText: Its dorsal and pectoral fins are strongly developed like muscles. It can swim at a speed of five knots.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Seaking
flavorText: Using its horn, it bores holes in riverbed boulders, making nests to prevent its eggs from washing away.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Staryu
flavorText: Fish Pokemon nibble at it, but Staryu isn't bothered. Its body regenerates quickly, even if part of it is completely torn off.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance, or by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Starmie
flavorText: Starmie swims by spinning its body at high speed. As this Pokemon cruises through the ocean, it absorbs tiny plankton.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may put 2 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. If you placed any damage counters in this way, discard this Pokemon and all attached cards.

name: Mr. Mime
flavorText: It's known for its top-notch pantomime skills. It protects itself from all sorts of attacks by emitting auras from its fingers to create walls.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon and your opponent's Active Pokemon have the same amount of Energy attached, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from your opponent's Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Scyther
flavorText: It slashes through grass with its sharp scythes, moving too fast for the human eye to track.
Attack1Text: Attach a Basic Grass Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Jynx ex
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is Asleep, it is Knocked Out.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Electabuzz
flavorText: With the coming of a storm, many of these Pokemon will gather under tall trees and sit there waiting for lightning to strike.
Attack1Text: If Magmar is on your Bench, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Magmar
flavorText: These Pokemon's bodies are constantly burning. Magmar are feared as one of the causes behind fires.
Attack2Text: If Electabuzz is on your Bench, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Pinsir
flavorText: This Pokemon clamps its pincers down on its prey and then either splits the prey in half or flings it away.
Attack2Text: If you have more Prize cards remaining than your opponent, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Tauros
flavorText: When it targets an enemy, it charges furiously while whipping its body with its long tails.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokemon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.

name: Magikarp
flavorText: An underpowered, pathetic Pokemon. It may jump high on rare occasions but never more than seven feet.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, draw a card.

name: Gyarados
flavorText: Once it appears, it goes on a rampage. It remains enraged until it demolishes everything around it.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you must discard the top 5 cards of your deck.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Lapras
flavorText: Crossing icy seas is no issue for this cold-resistant Pokemon. Its smooth skin is a little cool to the touch.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Pokemon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Ditto
flavorText: Its transformation ability is perfect. However, if made to laugh, it can't maintain its disguise.
Ability1Text: Once during your first turn, if this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, you may search your deck and choose a Basic Pokemon you find there, except any Ditto. If you do, discard this Pokemon and all attached cards, and put the chosen Pokemon in its place. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Eevee
evolvesTo: Vaporeon, Jolteon, Flareon, Sylveon, Espeon, Umbreon, Leafeon, Glaceon
flavorText: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 Pokemon of different types, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Vaporeon
flavorText: It lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin, which is often mistaken for a mermaid's.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon ex or Pokemon V, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Jolteon
flavorText: It concentrates the weak electric charges emitted by its cells and launches wicked lightning bolts.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon ex or Pokemon V, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Flareon
flavorText: Inhaled air is carried to its flame sac, heated, and exhaled as fire that reaches over 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon ex or Pokemon V, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Porygon
flavorText: In recent years, this species has been very helpful in cyberspace. These Pokemon will go around checking to make sure no suspicious data exists.
Attack1Text: Choose Grass, Fire, Water, Lightning, Psychic, Fighting, Darkness, Metal, or Dragon type. Until the Defending Pokemon leaves the Active Spot, its Weakness is now that type. (The amount of Weakness doesn't change.)

name: Omanyte
flavorText: This Pokemon is a member of an ancient, extinct species. Omanyte paddles through water with its 10 tentacles, looking like it's just drifting along.
Attack1Text: Put an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon into their hand.

name: Omastar
flavorText: Omastar's sharp fangs could crush rock, but the Pokemon can attack only the prey that come within reach of its tentacles.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, your opponent's Active Pokemon can't retreat.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Kabuto
flavorText: While some say this species has gone extinct, Kabuto sightings are apparently fairly common in some places.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 70 damage for each heads.

name: Kabutops
flavorText: The cause behind the extinction of this species is unknown. Kabutops were aggressive Pokemon that inhabited warm seas.
Ability1Text: Apply Weakness for your opponent's Active Pokemon as x4 instead.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Aerodactyl
flavorText: Aerodactyl's sawlike fangs can shred skin to tatters—even the skin of Steel-type Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is an evolved Pokemon, devolve it by putting the highest Stage Evolution card on it into your opponent's hand.

name: Snorlax
flavorText: This Pokemon's stomach is so strong, even eating moldy or rotten food will not affect it.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may put up to 2 Leftovers cards from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Articuno
flavorText: This Pokemon can control ice at will. Articuno is said to live in snowy mountains riddled with permafrost.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon has any Water Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Zapdos ex
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon has any Lightning Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 90 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon that has any damage counters on it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Moltres
flavorText: There are stories of this Pokemon using its radiant, flame-cloaked wings to light up paths for those lost in the mountains.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon has any Fire Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost.
Attack1Text: Discard 2 Fire Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 120 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Dratini
flavorText: It sheds many layers of skin as it grows larger. During this process, it is protected by a rapid waterfall.

name: Dragonair
flavorText: They say that if it emits an aura from its whole body, the weather will begin to change instantly.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Dragonite
flavorText: It is said that somewhere in the ocean lies an island where these gather. Only they live there.
Ability1Text: Your Pokemon in play have no Retreat Cost.
Attack1Text: Discard the top 2 cards of your deck.

name: Mewtwo
flavorText: A Pokemon created by recombining Mew's genes. It's said to have the most savage heart among Pokemon.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokemon is damaged by an attack (even if it is Knocked Out), put damage counters on the Attacking Pokemon equal to the damage done to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Mew ex
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may draw cards until you have 3 cards in your hand.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokemon's attacks and use it as this attack.

name: Antique Dome Fossil
Ability1Text: This Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Antique Helix Fossil
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, your opponent can't play any Stadium cards from their hand.

name: Antique Old Amber
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of your opponent's Pokemon's Abilities done to this Pokemon.

name: Bulbasaur
flavorText: While it is young, it uses the nutrients that are stored in the seed on its back in order to grow.
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Ivysaur
flavorText: Exposure to sunlight adds to its strength. Sunlight also makes the bud on its back grow larger.
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Charmander
flavorText: From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.
Attack1Text: Discard a Stadium in play.

name: Charmeleon
flavorText: If it becomes agitated during battle, it spouts intense flames, incinerating its surroundings.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Squirtle
flavorText: When it feels threatened, it draws its limbs inside its shell and sprays water from its mouth.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks.

name: Wartortle
flavorText: It cleverly controls its furry ears and tail to maintain its balance while swimming.
Attack1Text: Put up to 3 Basic Water Energy cards from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Caterpie
flavorText: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Grass Pokemon, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Lightning Energy card and attach it to this Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Nidoking
flavorText: Nidoking prides itself on its strength. It's forceful and spirited in battle, making use of its thick tail and diamond-crushing horn.
Ability1Text: If you have Nidoqueen in play, ignore all Energy in the costs of attacks used by this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Psyduck
flavorText: It is constantly wracked by a headache. When the headache turns intense, it begins using mysterious powers.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, whenever they flip a coin, treat it as tails.

name: Poliwhirl
flavorText: This Pokemon's sweat is a slimy mucus. When captured, Poliwhirl can slither from its enemies' grasp and escape.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Machoke
flavorText: Its formidable body never gets tired. It helps people by doing work such as the moving of heavy goods.
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

name: Tangela
flavorText: Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this Pokemon's true appearance remains a mystery.
Attack1Text: If you played Erika's Invitation from your hand during this turn, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Mr. Mime
flavorText: It's known for its top-notch pantomime skills. It protects itself from all sorts of attacks by emitting auras from its fingers to create walls.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon and your opponent's Active Pokemon have the same amount of Energy attached, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from your opponent's Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Pokemon in any way you like.

Attack1Text: Put an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon into their hand.
